    "causal_summary": "The generated graph-metadata status field is open. The normalizer normalizeDerivedStatus returns the raw normalized string in its default branch and the Zod schema accepts any non-empty string, so em-dash prose becomes a valid status. The shallow GRAPH_METADATA_SHAPE and DESCRIPTION_SHAPE checks run as warnings rather than a real gate, and the parser preserves a legacy bad status when a packet has no implementation-summary.md. The planned fix closes derived.status to a shared GRAPH_METADATA_STATUS_VALUES enum at the schema boundary so the normalizer returns an enum value or null, adds a first-class GENERATED_METADATA_INTEGRITY rule validating both JSON files through the shared schemas plus path-prefix and enum invariants registered as an error in strict mode behind a grandfather report mode, and stops preserving bad statuses by re-deriving on the closed enum or falling back to planned plus a review flag. Every behavioral fix ships behind a default-off flag or grandfather mode because existing files carry the prose statuses and prefixed paths the new contract rejects.",
